{{info}}
**Current Implementation (v2.11.0+)** - ClaimAssessmentBoundary pipeline. Uses 7-point symmetric verdict scale and 5-step LLM debate pattern.
{{/info}}

= Evidence and Verdict Data Model =

{{mermaid}}

erDiagram
    ATOMIC_CLAIM ||--o{ CB_CLAIM_VERDICT : receives
    CB_CLAIM_VERDICT }o--o{ EVIDENCE_ITEM : cited_by
    EVIDENCE_ITEM }o--|| SOURCE : from
    EVIDENCE_ITEM }o--|| CLAIM_ASSESSMENT_BOUNDARY : clustered_into

    ATOMIC_CLAIM {
        string id_PK
        string statement
        string category
        boolean isCentral
        float specificityScore
    }

    CB_CLAIM_VERDICT {
        string id_PK
        string claimId_FK
        string verdict "7-point scale"
        float truthPercentage
        float confidence
        string reasoning
        json boundaryFindings
        json challengeResponses
    }

    EVIDENCE_ITEM {
        string id_PK
        string sourceUrl
        string statement
        string sourceExcerpt
        string probativeValue "high|medium|low"
        json evidenceScope
    }

    SOURCE {
        string id_PK
        string url
        float trackRecordScore
        string sourceType
    }

{{/mermaid}}

= Verdict Generation Flow (Stage 4) =

{{mermaid}}

flowchart TB
    subgraph Research[Evidence Input]
        EVIDENCE[Clustered Evidence Items]
        BOUNDARIES[ClaimAssessmentBoundaries]
    end

    subgraph Debate["Stage 4: LLM Debate Pattern (verdict-stage.ts)"]
        ADV["1. Advocate\n(Build pro-case)"]
        CONS["2. Consistency\n(Identify unstable areas)"]
        CHAL["3. Challenger\n(Attack weaknesses)"]
        RECON["4. Reconciler\n(Synthesize final view)"]
        VAL["5. Validation\n(Structural & Grounding)"]
        ADV --> CONS --> CHAL --> RECON --> VAL
    end

    subgraph Finalize["Stage 5: Aggregation"]
        WEIGHT["Weight by Specificity\nand Probative Value"]
        TRIANG["Source Triangulation"]
        NARR["Generate Narrative"]
        WEIGHT --> TRIANG --> NARR
    end

    EVIDENCE --> ADV
    BOUNDARIES --> ADV
    VAL --> WEIGHT
    NARR --> RESULT["AnalysisResult"]

{{/mermaid}}

== 7-Point Verdict Scale ==

|= Verdict |= Truth % Range |= Description
| **TRUE** | 86-100% | Claim is well-supported by evidence
| **MOSTLY-TRUE** | 72-85% | Largely accurate with minor caveats
| **LEANING-TRUE** | 58-71% | More evidence supports than contradicts
| **MIXED** | 43-57% (high conf) | Roughly equal evidence both ways
| **UNVERIFIED** | 43-57% (low conf) | Insufficient evidence to determine
| **LEANING-FALSE** | 29-42% | More evidence contradicts than supports
| **MOSTLY-FALSE** | 15-28% | Largely inaccurate
| **FALSE** | 0-14% | Claim is refuted by evidence

== Contestation Status ==

* **Doubted**: Evidence is weak, uncertain, or ambiguous
* **Contested**: Strong evidence exists on both sides

== Source Reliability ==

Source reliability scores use **LLM + Cache architecture** (v2.2):
* LLM-based assessment with in-memory caching
* Batch prefetch → in-memory map → sync lookup
* Configurable via UCM SR config (##source-reliability.ts##)